            "summary": "Dell Technologies (NYSE: DELL) has released its financial outcomes for the first quarter of fiscal 2026, indicating promising statistics. The company recorded a first-quarter revenue of $23.4 billion, representing a 5% increase compared to the previous year. Moreover, first-quarter operating income saw significant growth, reaching $1.2 billion, a remarkable 21% surge year over year. The non-GAAP operating income also demonstrated a positive trend, standing at $1.7 billion, marking a 10% increase. The first-quarter diluted EPS amounted to $1.37, maintaining stability compared to the previous year. Dell Technologies additionally provided guidance for the fiscal 2026 second quarter and full year, indicating a positive outlook for the future.",
